[TestRuleDependencyCheck/warns_about_bar:sum_but_ignores_foo:sum_when_only_foo:.*_is_in_ignoreGroupMismatch - 1]
- description: warns about bar:sum but ignores foo:sum when only foo:.* is in ignoreGroupMismatch
  content: |
    groups:
    - name: aggregations
      rules:
      - record: combined:rate
        expr: rate(foo:sum[5m]) + rate(bar:sum[5m])
  output: |
    5 |     expr: rate(foo:sum[5m]) + rate(bar:sum[5m])
                                           ^^^^^^^ Rule uses `bar:sum` which is generated by a recording rule in a different group `base`.
  problem:
    reporter: rule/dependency
    summary: rule uses metric produced by a recording rule from a different group
    details: |-
        This rule uses `bar:sum` which is generated by a recording rule in the `base` group at `base.yaml:6`.
        Rules in different groups are evaluated independently. This rule may use data from the previous evaluation cycle, introducing up to one evaluation interval of lag. Moving both rules to the same group ensures they are evaluated together with consistent data.
    diagnostics:
        - message: Rule uses `bar:sum` which is generated by a recording rule in a different group `base`.
          firstcolumn: 26
          lastcolumn: 32
          kind: 0
    lines:
        first: 5
        last: 5
    severity: 1
    anchor: 0

---

